    "body": "### Problem\n\n`menu_info` returns incorrect information\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\r\nnvim --clean\r\n```\r\n\r\n```vim\r\n# Create 3 menu items, each for a different mode\r\n:nnoremenu Menu.Item1 <cmd>echo 'normal item1'<cr>\r\n:vnoremenu Menu.Item1 <cmd>echo 'visual item1'<cr>\r\n:inoremenu Menu.Item1 <cmd>echo 'insert item1'<cr>\r\n\r\n# Echo the information for insert mode item 1\r\n:echo menu_info('Menu.Item1', 'i')\r\n\r\n# Add another item only for normal mode, and output the submenus for visual mode\r\n:nnoremenu Menu.Item2 <cmd>echo 'normal item2'<cr>\r\n:echo menu_info('Menu', 'v').submenus\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nHere's the output information for insert mode item 1:\r\n\r\n```vim\r\n{\r\n    'modes': 'v',\r\n    'script': v:false,\r\n    'name': 'Item1',\r\n    'priority': 500,\r\n    'enabled': v:true,\r\n    'shortcut': '',\r\n    'silent': v:false,\r\n    'rhs': ' <Cmd>echo ''insert item1''<CR>',\r\n    'display': 'Item1',\r\n    'noremenu': v:true\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt says `'modes': 'v'`, whereas I expected this to be `'modes': 'i'`.\r\n\r\nHere's the output information for visual mode submenus:\r\n\r\n```vim\r\n['Item1', 'Item2']\r\n```\r\n\r\nI expected this to be `['Item1']`, since no `'Item2'` item was added for visual mode.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.10.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nKubuntu 24.04\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nKonsole 23.08.5\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
